@startuml ThrobberAnimator Class Diagram
!theme plain
title "ThrobberAnimator - Thread-Safe Loading Animation Component"

package "terminal::throbber" {
    class ThrobberAnimator {
        - index: Arc<AtomicUsize>
        - active: Arc<AtomicBool>
        - thread_handle: Mutex<Option<JoinHandle<()>>>

        + new() -> Self
        + start() -> void
        + stop() -> void
        + is_running() -> bool
        + symbol() -> &'static str
        + frame_index() -> usize
    }
}

package "std::sync" {
    class AtomicUsize
    class AtomicBool
    class Arc<T>
    class Mutex<T>
}

package "std::thread" {
    class JoinHandle<T>
}

package "throbber_widgets_tui" {
    class BRAILLE_DOUBLE {
        symbols: &'static [&'static str]
    }
}

' Relationships
ThrobberAnimator --> Arc : uses Arc<AtomicUsize>
ThrobberAnimator --> Arc : uses Arc<AtomicBool>
Arc --> AtomicUsize : wraps
Arc --> AtomicBool : wraps
ThrobberAnimator --> Mutex : wraps thread_handle
Mutex --> JoinHandle : contains

' Animation thread interaction
note right of ThrobberAnimator
  Spawns dedicated animation thread that:
  - Increments index every 100ms (~10 FPS)
  - Reads/writes atomically (lock-free)
  - Exits when 'active' flag becomes false

  Thread Safety:
  - All methods are thread-safe
  - start() is idempotent
  - Uses SeqCst ordering for start/stop
  - Uses Relaxed ordering for hot path
end note

note right of BRAILLE_DOUBLE
  Braille double dot unicode symbols
  for smooth loading animation
end note

@enduml
